Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_2911
Response Text: Oh, where to begin! Professional panelists who are held accountable to the stated guidelines. Our organization had the SAME panelist TWO years in a row, who did not do a professional job reviewing applications. How is it that the SAME panelist was assigned to our org two years in a row? I am dumbfounded

Lack of transparency. I was part of numerous feedback sessions with city staff, arts commissioners, and consultants during the last round of revising Cultural funding. I was never given any of the data that was collected from those sessions. I did not receive any explanation of how our feedback was going to be included in the revision. And then, I heard recently that the Cultural Funding is being reviewed once again. (I don't get an email, I hear this at an Arts Commission meeting). 

I am flabbergasted. And then, we are told no funding in 2025 for programs running Oct - Dec of 2025. What? Our major program this year is in November. It did not qualify for funding last round, and now it is going to be "skipped" in this next round of funding? That is unacceptable. 

I am an internationally known artist who is a thought leader and master level artist in my field, and I find my hometown of Austin, Texas, to be very unsupportive of artists and arts organizations. Please get organized. Don't ask us to give you more feedback if you haven't read all of the feedback WE HAVE ALREADY given you. And DON'T CHANGE FUNDING GUIDELINES with less than a year of warning. Treat artists with respect and professionalism. We are the heart of this city.

